WEBVTT

00:00.898 --> 00:01.780
Good morning everybody.

00:01.901 --> 00:02.883
Welcome to church.

00:03.224 --> 00:05.329
All you guys in the room and online.

00:05.790 --> 00:06.773
We're so glad that you're here.

00:06.793 --> 00:08.136
He chose to spend church.

00:08.798 --> 00:10.161
Making a priority to be here.

00:10.342 --> 00:12.989
We're going to sing to our God who deserves our praise.

00:13.009 --> 00:15.154
Can we stand to our feet and give Him glory?

16:25.730 --> 16:26.931
We give you our praise.

16:28.733 --> 16:29.874
We give you this time.

16:29.935 --> 16:36.902
We declare in these songs that we trust you, that we believe deeply that you are in control.

16:39.565 --> 16:46.012
But you call us to love people as you love people and see people as you see people.

16:47.473 --> 16:49.075
So give us the eyes to do that.

16:51.017 --> 16:55.442
Help us to respond to the way you love us by loving others.

16:55.618 --> 16:56.079
the same.

16:57.602 --> 16:58.183
You're not done.

16:58.223 --> 17:08.763
Teach us something new in this message so that we can be more like you when we leave here in a world that so desperately needs you, Jesus.

17:08.783 --> 17:09.825
Thank you for this time.

17:09.865 --> 17:12.810
Thank you for these people, I pray in Jesus' name.

17:14.073 --> 17:15.435
Amen.

17:15.455 --> 17:15.716
Amen.

17:15.776 --> 17:17.139
My friends, good to be with you.

17:17.219 --> 17:18.301
Good to worship with you.

17:18.321 --> 17:18.962
You can take a seat.

17:23.746 --> 17:25.908
Well, hey everyone and welcome to Eagle Brook Online.

17:25.968 --> 17:26.929
My name is Jeff Dodge.

17:27.029 --> 17:28.350
I'm the online campus pastor.

17:28.470 --> 17:31.353
And earlier this week, I decided what I wanted to talk about this weekend.

17:31.693 --> 17:36.337
And then just a couple of days later, I was reading my Bible and I felt like this passage leapt off the page.

17:36.357 --> 17:37.618
And so I want to share it with you today.

17:38.058 --> 17:43.123
It's from the Apostle Paul's writings in the book of Colossians chapter two, beginning in verse nine.

17:43.263 --> 17:53.732
It talks about Jesus and how the fullness of God dwells in him, which is Bible speak for Jesus is God and how we have been filled in him through faith.

17:53.712 --> 17:59.181
It says this rather odd statement that in Christ we have been circumcised without hands.

17:59.742 --> 18:02.206
If you don't know what circumcision is, go ask your parents.

18:02.306 --> 18:09.879
But why this phrase is important was because under the Old Covenant, circumcision was the way that people entered into an agreement with God.

18:09.999 --> 18:12.143
It was what set God's people apart.

18:12.243 --> 18:14.066
It was the way that God marked

18:14.178 --> 18:14.979
His people.

18:15.019 --> 18:24.650
And what Paul is saying here is that today, the way that we set ourselves apart, the way that we are mark ourselves as children of God is through faith in Jesus.

18:25.011 --> 18:27.754
And that is how we enter into covenant with God.

18:27.774 --> 18:32.800
And then it goes on to say that we are buried with Christ in baptism.

18:33.241 --> 18:36.444
And then we're raised to a new life through faith in Jesus.

18:36.545 --> 18:41.170
Essentially saying that after entering into covenant with God through faith in Jesus,

18:41.250 --> 18:44.498
Our very next step is to be buried with him

18:44.546 --> 18:58.428
in baptism, symbolically demonstrating that the sin that once controlled us has no claim to us now, that we've died to it, and that through faith, we are made new creations set apart and marked as God's people.

18:58.808 --> 19:02.174
Here and in many other places in Scripture, it is very clear.

19:02.514 --> 19:06.140
If you've put your faith in Jesus, then it's time to be baptized.

19:06.501 --> 19:12.530
Maybe you've just recently made that decision, or maybe you've been a believer for a long time but haven't yet taken this step.

19:12.578 --> 19:14.240
Don't let any more time pass.

19:14.520 --> 19:19.607
We are doing baptisms at all of our campuses on the weekend of February 7th and 8th.

19:19.927 --> 19:26.015
To find your nearest campus and to register, head to eaglebrookchurch.com slash baptism.

19:26.415 --> 19:31.021
And you might notice that we don't have an online option for winter baptism.

19:31.382 --> 19:33.925
In years past, virtually no one would sign up.

19:34.265 --> 19:40.353
And now we put our heads together and we realized that it's almost like people don't like to travel to Minnesota in the dead of winter.

19:40.373 --> 19:41.234
And so we thought,

19:41.346 --> 19:42.860
Where do people like to travel?

19:43.344 --> 19:44.434
The answer is Florida.

19:44.610 --> 19:46.993
Okay, now we're gonna do online baptisms there.

19:47.414 --> 19:59.089
Seriously, we have multiple viewing groups in Southwest Florida, and we're gonna be attending two of them on Sunday, February 8th, and then going to the ocean to baptize as many people as we can.

19:59.129 --> 20:11.986
If you're visiting or if you live in that area and you wanna join us for a service or to get baptized somewhere a little bit more tropical, let us know by emailing me at online at eaglebrookchurch.com.

20:12.514 --> 20:17.010
And as you're doing that, I'm gonna hand it back to the band.

24:30.818 --> 24:31.259
So good.

24:31.299 --> 24:37.210
Today, before I jump into the message, I want to talk a little bit about some of the events in our world.

24:37.811 --> 24:43.182
It seems like every weekend there's something in the national news that's happening in Minneapolis.

24:44.765 --> 24:51.458
Almost every weekend I get a text message from a friend, you know, someplace in Texas or California saying, oh my goodness, what's going on in Minnesota?

24:52.460 --> 24:53.682
It's going on in Minneapolis.

24:54.562 --> 25:01.430
And you probably have opinions as to why that is, and I have opinions as to why that is, but here's a verse from the Bible that God has been bringing me to this week.

25:02.250 --> 25:07.937
It's from Ephesians chapter six, verse 12, for our struggle is not against flesh and blood.

25:10.379 --> 25:11.841
Our struggle is not against people.

25:13.363 --> 25:14.524
We tend to think it is.

25:14.544 --> 25:19.009
We tend to think it's politicians, people on the other side, people who just don't understand.

25:19.229 --> 25:23.794
We think the battle is primarily against people, but here's what he says, really our struggle.

25:24.418 --> 25:32.369
is against the rulers, against the authorities, against the powers of this dark world, and against the spiritual forces of evil in the heavenly realms.

25:34.172 --> 25:36.275
That there is a spiritual battle taking place.

25:37.697 --> 25:40.340
And we can't see that spiritual battle with our physical eyes.

25:40.481 --> 25:41.502
I can't see that battle.

25:41.582 --> 25:42.564
You can't see that battle.

25:42.824 --> 25:46.249
But we see the effects of that battle.

25:46.269 --> 25:52.818
And so over the course of the last week or so, as I've been reading this verse and reflecting on it, I become convinced there is a spiritual battle.

25:53.442 --> 25:56.387
over the city of Minneapolis.

25:56.407 --> 26:02.316
And as followers of Christ, I would love to show you this verse in Second Chronicles and call you to this.

26:02.757 --> 26:20.626
He says, if my people who are called by my name, that's us, will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then he says, I will hear from heaven and I will forgive their sin and I will heal their land.

26:22.306 --> 26:23.568
Does our land need to be healed?

26:25.830 --> 26:27.092
Yes, our land needs to be healed.

26:28.694 --> 26:41.269
I wanna invite you as a church this week, every day this week at 714, the verse we just read, 2 Chronicles 714, at 714 every day, set an alarm on your phone to be praying that God would heal our land.

26:42.831 --> 26:45.194
Now the question some of you are wondering is AM or PM?

26:46.615 --> 26:48.077
And I'm just gonna let you decide, okay?

26:48.438 --> 26:52.082
Depending on your lifestyle and how you live your life, you can choose.

26:54.818 --> 26:58.982
But at 714, to set an alarm on your phone and to say, God, would you heal our land?

27:00.504 --> 27:06.970
Humble ourselves and come before him and pray and seek his face and say, God, would you heal our city?

27:08.131 --> 27:12.656
Kyle Eidelman who's spoken at our church before is that he's a pastor at a church in Kentucky.

27:12.716 --> 27:14.037
He sent me this early in the week.

27:14.057 --> 27:15.078
He sent me this on Monday.

27:15.999 --> 27:22.546
And this is the elders from his church and they're down praying and they're praying for us.

27:24.482 --> 27:39.297
sent me a text and said, we were praying for Eaglebrook Church that you would be a light, that you would be full of God's truth and full of God's grace, that you'd be full of His mercy and His justice, and they were praying for God to heal our land and our state and our city.

27:40.559 --> 27:41.479
And so I wanna join them.

27:42.561 --> 27:46.665
Let's take a moment, let's pray, and let's ask God to do just that.

27:50.449 --> 27:51.730
Lord, right now in this moment,

27:53.890 --> 27:55.292
we humble ourselves before you.

27:58.677 --> 28:09.892
We turn from the news and everything that we are bombarded with every day, God, and we turn our face to you and we seek you in this moment.

28:12.295 --> 28:17.362
And God, we ask in the name of Jesus that you would heal our land, that you would heal our city.

28:20.994 --> 28:26.620
God, I pray for victory over the spiritual battle that takes place, the spiritual battle in the heavenly realms.

28:26.740 --> 28:32.485
I pray for victory right now over the powers, principalities and rulers of this dark world.

28:34.207 --> 28:37.851
And we pray it in Jesus' name.

28:37.871 --> 28:40.113
All right, today we are gonna continue on in our series.

28:40.153 --> 28:42.595
We've been in for the last several weeks called Cabin Fever.

28:42.615 --> 28:44.397
This is actually the last week of this series.

28:44.417 --> 28:45.718
It's been all about relationships.

28:46.159 --> 28:49.362
And I wanna start today with a joke that I heard recently

28:49.474 --> 28:52.419
It was about a husband and a wife and the husband had a rare disease.

28:53.280 --> 28:54.863
And the doctor wasn't sure he was gonna make it.

28:54.883 --> 28:56.906
And so the doctor pulled the wife into the hallway.

28:56.926 --> 28:58.669
He said, I'm gonna kind of break this to you first.

28:58.969 --> 29:00.993
Then you can go break the news to your husband.

29:01.594 --> 29:03.797
So he said to her, he said, your husband has this rare disease.

29:04.258 --> 29:05.380
I don't think he's gonna make it.

29:05.400 --> 29:09.466
But if he is gonna make it, he needs to live a life with no stress.

29:10.708 --> 29:13.733
So he needs to wake up in the morning to a hot meal prepared by you.

29:13.773 --> 29:16.658
He needs to have the house spotless.

29:17.634 --> 29:19.736
He needs a life conducive to rest.

29:19.756 --> 29:20.938
So don't ask him to do chores.

29:21.258 --> 29:22.439
Don't upset him in any way.

29:23.320 --> 29:25.623
He needs you to be pleasant at all times.

29:26.263 --> 29:27.525
So don't bring your problems.

29:27.585 --> 29:28.726
Don't bring your emotions.

29:29.347 --> 29:32.711
He said, if you can do that, I think there's a chance that your husband could live.

29:33.451 --> 29:36.555
A wife went back into the husband's hospital room.

29:36.575 --> 29:38.577
He was obviously anxious to hear what the doctor had said.

29:38.597 --> 29:39.658
He said, what did the doctor say?

29:39.698 --> 29:43.122
She looked at him and she said, he said, you're going to die.

29:48.418 --> 29:50.821
Wouldn't we love a marriage where there's no stress?

29:51.942 --> 30:00.291
I mean, it's just a hot meal every day and the house is spotless, no problems, no emotions, no annoyances, no frustrations.

30:01.372 --> 30:05.997
If you are waiting for that in your relationships, you are gonna be waiting until heaven.

30:07.198 --> 30:14.546
When I used to do weddings, I would look at the soon to be husband and the soon to be wife, and I would say, when you take one sinful person,

30:14.946 --> 30:19.113
and you marry them to another sinful person, you don't get less sin.

30:20.154 --> 30:21.737
Amazing how that ends up working out.

30:22.859 --> 30:26.945
But part of the problem that marriages today face is with our expectations.

30:27.947 --> 30:30.310
We have been told this other person is gonna complete you.

30:31.132 --> 30:38.443
This other person, they're gonna meet all of your needs and they're always gonna buy you the perfect Christmas gift, just like they do on the Hallmark movies.

30:39.645 --> 30:42.770
Here's the reality, marriage is hard.

30:44.866 --> 30:46.649
We don't hear that enough, but it is.

30:48.251 --> 30:49.553
Anybody can fall in love.

30:49.674 --> 30:50.916
All you need for that is a pulse.

30:52.258 --> 30:56.104
But what's never been more difficult is to stay in love.

30:56.745 --> 31:00.090
In fact, sometimes you'll hear people today and they'll say, you know, we fell out of love.

31:01.112 --> 31:05.779
And when I hear people say that, I notice that they're treating love as if it's a noun and not a verb.

31:06.821 --> 31:09.405
I fell out of love.

31:09.425 --> 31:10.627
Well, what's the thing I fell out of?

31:10.647 --> 31:12.850
Well, the thing, the noun is love.

31:13.762 --> 31:16.947
But love isn't a noun, love is a verb.

31:17.828 --> 31:25.701
If you said to me, I fell out of my truck, I'd say, well, why don't you climb back up in your truck again?

31:25.761 --> 31:29.827
And that's what I want to say to some of us today in your marriage.

31:31.490 --> 31:32.972
What if you fell back in love again?

31:34.795 --> 31:36.978
What if you climbed back up in your marriage again?

31:38.146 --> 31:41.772
And I don't say that flippantly because I know some of you are like, Hey, you don't know my situation.

31:41.993 --> 31:42.954
You don't know what I've been through.

31:43.195 --> 31:44.918
You don't know what he or she did to me.

31:44.998 --> 31:45.599
And you're right.

31:45.699 --> 31:49.967
I don't know your situation, but I do know your God.

31:52.211 --> 31:57.520
He's a God of hope and he's a God of healing and he's a God of restoration and he is a God of miracles.

31:59.383 --> 32:02.128
Here's what the Bible says about marriage and Ephesians chapter five.

32:02.168 --> 32:03.090
It says husbands,

32:04.322 --> 32:10.069
Love your wives just as Christ loved the church and gave himself up for her.

32:12.552 --> 32:20.482
Love is a willingness to sacrifice, it's a willingness to sacrifice what we want for the sake of what another person needs.

32:22.144 --> 32:24.567
Some of us can't even imagine what that would be like, can we?

32:26.089 --> 32:30.515
You might sleep two feet apart at night, but it feels like there is a two mile gap.

32:31.796 --> 32:33.138
This is between the two of you right now.

32:34.946 --> 32:37.569
You can't even imagine feeling loved by that person again.

32:37.830 --> 32:40.713
You can't imagine loving that person again.

32:40.733 --> 32:43.977
I wanna take you to Revelation chapter two.

32:44.838 --> 32:50.685
And this is a verse, it's not specifically about marriage, but I think it has a lot of application to marriage.

32:51.146 --> 32:53.909
Jesus is speaking directly here to the church in Ephesus.

32:54.430 --> 32:57.394
And he compliments them in all kinds of different ways and says, here's some great things you're doing.

32:57.934 --> 33:00.978
But then he says this, he says, yet I hold this against you.

33:02.050 --> 33:04.773
You have forsaken the love you had at first.

33:05.895 --> 33:07.998
Consider how far you have fallen.

33:09.119 --> 33:13.625
Repent and do the things you did at first.

33:15.267 --> 33:18.591
Jesus is talking about a time in our life when you loved God more than you do today.

33:18.611 --> 33:27.122
And maybe you can think of a time like that where you're like, yeah, I loved God more when I was in college or I loved God more several years ago than I do today.

33:28.322 --> 33:33.090
And if that's you, Jesus' message to you is to repent and do the things you did at first.

33:34.072 --> 33:39.361
Repent, which means turn around, acknowledge where you're at, go in the other direction.

33:40.342 --> 33:42.205
And then he says, do the things you did at first.

33:43.347 --> 33:49.778
So if you loved God more when you were a part of a small group and people were encouraging you in your faith, get into a small group again.

33:50.690 --> 33:57.000
If you felt like you loved God more when you were sharing your faith and you were around non-believers, well, then start doing that again.

33:57.281 --> 33:59.204
Do the things you did at first.

34:00.526 --> 34:02.209
Think about how this applies to our marriages.

34:03.290 --> 34:08.499
When we first start dating, oftentimes you write these, you know, just sweet notes.

34:09.500 --> 34:12.365
You're just my little ooby booby tooby wooshy.

34:12.565 --> 34:14.889
You know, you're just these little sweet notes.

34:15.891 --> 34:18.034
You'd play on these creative dates.

34:19.586 --> 34:23.211
You would pour time and energy into that relationship.

34:23.272 --> 34:29.140
You would drive an hour to spend a half hour with that person and then drive an hour back home.

34:30.002 --> 34:31.624
I'm not necessarily saying you do that again.

34:32.966 --> 34:34.909
But what if you did the things you did at first?

34:36.511 --> 34:43.602
What if you wrote an encouraging note, planned a creative date, spent some quality time with one another?

34:44.962 --> 34:48.367
Whenever I talk to couples about this, the pushback that I'll get is, well, I don't feel that way anymore.

34:48.407 --> 34:52.733
You know, I felt that way then, that's why I did those things, but now I don't feel that way anymore.

34:54.535 --> 34:57.820
Notice that the verse doesn't say, repent if you feel like it.

34:59.882 --> 35:03.988
It doesn't say, when you start feeling like it, well then maybe you should do the things you did at first.

35:04.228 --> 35:07.934
He simply says repent and do the things you did at first.

35:09.396 --> 35:11.218
Your feelings will often follow.

35:12.354 --> 35:17.440
You start pouring time and energy and effort into your relationship with God, often your feelings will follow.

35:18.121 --> 35:23.967
You start pouring time and energy and effort into your marriage, and often your feelings will follow.

35:25.049 --> 35:28.773
Maybe you're here today and you're happily married, kind of.

35:30.034 --> 35:32.958
But there's just something in your marriage where you go, hey, I'm a little bit unfulfilled.

35:33.058 --> 35:35.140
I feel a little bit unhappy in marriage.

35:36.362 --> 35:40.306
My wife Sarah and I sat down last Sunday night, and we had a really good conversation.

35:41.218 --> 35:44.964
about some of the areas in our marriage where we felt unhappy and we felt unfulfilled.

35:46.647 --> 35:47.067
And that's just it.

35:47.087 --> 35:49.371
Some people think, well, all these other marriages are doing so great.

35:49.391 --> 35:50.333
My marriage is struggling.

35:50.713 --> 35:52.015
That is simply not true.

35:52.957 --> 35:58.305
Every single marriage, every single relationship goes through natural ups and downs.

35:59.247 --> 36:01.150
If you ask me, how is your marriage doing?

36:01.350 --> 36:02.272
Depends on the day.

36:03.474 --> 36:04.395
Yesterday not great.

36:04.415 --> 36:06.118
Today we're doing awesome.

36:06.138 --> 36:07.420
Last week was a little bit rough.

36:07.460 --> 36:08.722
This week is really, really good.

36:09.634 --> 36:12.758
Every relationship has natural ups and downs.

36:12.778 --> 36:21.227
So the question is this, how do you go the long haul, even with all the natural ups and downs that relationships and marriages have?

36:22.028 --> 36:25.392
The first way is this, eliminate the D word.

36:26.653 --> 36:29.897
It is a study at the University of Chicago where they ask couples a really simple question.

36:30.137 --> 36:31.519
How happy are you in your marriage?

36:32.801 --> 36:35.003
And maybe you wanna even answer that question in your mind right now.

36:35.043 --> 36:36.104
Am I happily married?

36:36.144 --> 36:37.586
Am I unhappily married?

36:38.050 --> 36:39.712
Here was the interesting part of the study.

36:39.752 --> 36:46.880
They found that of those who said they were unhappy in their marriage, they traced them for five years.

36:46.941 --> 36:48.382
They stuck with them for five years.

36:48.643 --> 36:50.965
They asked them the same question five years later.

36:52.387 --> 37:02.599
And for those that stayed married and worked through those issues, over two thirds of them were now in the very happily married category.

37:04.181 --> 37:05.042
Five years.

37:06.914 --> 37:16.284
All they had to do was push through those issues, work through those problems, and they went in five years from saying, I am unhappy in my marriage, to I am extremely happy in my marriage.

37:18.025 --> 37:18.946
What if that could be you?

37:20.808 --> 37:22.510
Here's a phrase I hope that you will remember.

37:22.930 --> 37:27.015
Our marriage will be as good as we decide it will be.

37:27.075 --> 37:29.297
You decide.

37:31.139 --> 37:34.322
You can spend money on a counselor, or you can spend money on a boat, but you decide.

37:35.746 --> 37:39.551
You can scroll on TikTok or you can read a book about marriage but you decide.

37:41.594 --> 37:46.560
You can keep a record of wrongs and store up bitterness in your heart or you can forgive but you decide.

37:47.942 --> 37:52.428
You can pray for your marriage or you can not pray for your marriage but you decide.

37:54.030 --> 37:57.935
Now, when I say you decide, here's the scenario that's so tricky about that.

37:58.216 --> 38:00.018
Some of you might say, hey, I want to.

38:00.706 --> 38:01.908
I wanna work on our marriage.

38:01.988 --> 38:02.750
I wanna go to church.

38:02.790 --> 38:04.333
I wanna pray about our marriage.

38:04.353 --> 38:05.475
I wanna go see a counselor.

38:05.695 --> 38:06.537
I wanna read the book.

38:06.817 --> 38:07.318
They don't.

38:08.801 --> 38:09.763
My husband refuses.

38:09.823 --> 38:10.664
My wife refuses.

38:10.725 --> 38:11.145
They won't.

38:13.149 --> 38:17.717
How do you grow in a happy, healthy marriage with someone who doesn't want to work on the marriage?

38:19.000 --> 38:22.386
This is one of the scenarios that I see Satan use more than almost any other.

38:23.234 --> 38:25.918
And this is a bit of a generalization, but this is just from my own experience.

38:26.338 --> 38:31.465
Oftentimes it's the wife who says, I wanna go to counseling, I wanna go to church, I wanna pray about our marriage.

38:32.667 --> 38:34.810
And for whatever reason, the husband kind of drags his feet.

38:36.512 --> 38:40.177
And he's busy and he's got other things going on and he just doesn't wanna do it.

38:40.217 --> 38:44.443
Maybe there's some pride involved, but there's just something in him that's like, I don't wanna do that.

38:46.085 --> 38:49.891
And then all of a sudden she just kind of snaps and she goes, that's it, I'm done.

38:49.931 --> 38:52.274
That's it.

38:53.698 --> 38:54.960
And you know what the husband does at that point?

38:55.240 --> 38:59.887
I'll go to church, I'll pray, I'll go to counseling, I'll do whatever you want.

38:59.907 --> 39:01.970
But at that point, she's already made the decision.

39:03.533 --> 39:08.460
I see Satan use that situation to destroy more marriages than almost any other.

39:10.042 --> 39:12.526
What do you do if you are married to a non-believer?

39:12.566 --> 39:17.333
Cause some of you might be in that situation where you're like, I came to church, they didn't, I bring the kids, they don't come.

39:18.475 --> 39:20.638
The Bible speaks directly to that situation.

39:20.658 --> 39:23.442
1 Peter chapter three, here's what it says.

39:24.770 --> 39:42.238
Your husband does, if your husband does not believe the word, okay, so he doesn't believe the word, not a follower of Christ, they may be won over without words by the behavior of their wives when they see the purity and reverence of your lives.

39:44.021 --> 39:49.970
What he's saying is if you're in that situation, words aren't going to be often your best strategy.

39:52.034 --> 39:55.118
The words of like nagging, like, why don't you be more of a spiritual leader?

39:55.138 --> 39:56.200
Why don't you do more of these things?

39:56.600 --> 39:58.904
Probably isn't your best approach.

39:59.124 --> 40:01.207
Your best approach is to live a godly life.

40:02.329 --> 40:04.792
And they would see that godly life and they would be drawn to it.

40:05.954 --> 40:08.998
Now I wanna point out, this is a principle, not a promise.

40:10.741 --> 40:16.589
It's not 100% guaranteed that if you live a godly life that your spouse is gonna see that and go, you know what, I really want that in my life.

40:17.871 --> 40:20.274
But it's probably the best bet.

40:21.058 --> 40:33.931
If I could speak to the husband or wife who doesn't want to go to counseling, who doesn't want to work on the marriage, that when my wife or I first got married, we went to see a counselor a couple of years in, and I was the one who didn't want to go.

40:35.293 --> 40:36.474
And here was my argument to my wife.

40:36.494 --> 40:37.996
I'm like, we don't need to go to counseling.

40:38.536 --> 40:39.297
What, they got a degree?

40:39.617 --> 40:43.461
They got a four year degree, read some books, got a little diploma on the wall.

40:43.481 --> 40:44.162
They're just a person.

40:44.402 --> 40:45.303
We've got wisdom.

40:45.323 --> 40:46.624
We can figure this out on our own.

40:46.664 --> 40:48.146
We don't need to go see a counselor.

40:49.250 --> 40:52.917
And maybe there was a little pride involved, because when I went in, I was kind of like, oh, no one sees me here.

40:55.201 --> 40:56.603
But I'm so glad that we did.

40:56.643 --> 40:58.787
I grew from that.

40:58.928 --> 41:00.210
Our marriage grew from that.

41:01.332 --> 41:13.394
If you're here today and you're resisting, I would urge you to take that step for your sake, for your marriage's sake, for your kids and the marriage that they watch and see every single day.

41:14.754 --> 41:19.703
For your legacy of your life and with your family and with your grandchildren, take that step.

41:21.286 --> 41:25.653
I know spouses who their spouse comes to them and says, hey, you need to stop drinking.

41:25.673 --> 41:26.795
You stop abusing the substance.

41:26.956 --> 41:27.537
They won't do it.

41:29.099 --> 41:30.141
And I'm like, it's a liquid.

41:31.303 --> 41:32.005
It's a beverage.

41:32.025 --> 41:32.806
It doesn't love you.

41:32.846 --> 41:36.012
It's trick the chemicals of your brain to make you think, I need this.

41:36.132 --> 41:37.354
I can't function without it.

41:37.815 --> 41:39.538
Your marriage needs you.

41:41.218 --> 41:46.044
Do whatever it takes, go to treatment, do whatever it takes.

41:47.045 --> 41:48.928
Here's what I've noticed happens in a lot of marriages.

41:49.248 --> 41:54.255
We get married to someone and at first, when we're dating or when we're first married, we love everything about him.

41:55.096 --> 41:56.678
I mean, just go ask a young couple, what do you like?

41:56.698 --> 41:57.359
Oh, he's perfect.

41:58.220 --> 41:59.021
She's perfect.

41:59.041 --> 42:01.023
100% love everything about him.

42:02.045 --> 42:06.450
Six months into marriage, a year into marriage, certainly by five years into marriage, you're like 80%.

42:08.373 --> 42:09.394
I love 80% of them.

42:11.074 --> 42:15.280
But there's 20% of what you want in that marriage and in that relationship that's missing.

42:15.921 --> 42:19.406
80% of what you love, 20% of what you want is missing.

42:19.666 --> 42:22.770
And over the years, we start to long for that 20%.

42:24.192 --> 42:26.375
So we start to think things like, I wish he was more thoughtful.

42:27.898 --> 42:29.960
And I wish he was more fun and adventurous.

42:29.980 --> 42:31.563
You know, I'm kind of losing that in myself.

42:31.603 --> 42:33.646
And I wish he was more of a spiritual leader.

42:33.686 --> 42:39.634
And then you meet someone in the neighborhood, at work, in your friend group,

42:39.842 --> 42:41.444
and they have the 20%.

42:42.726 --> 42:45.651
And you're so drawn to that 20%, you chase that 20%.

42:45.911 --> 42:53.243
And all of a sudden, either emotionally or physically, you start drifting from your marriage into this other relationship.

42:54.665 --> 42:56.768
And at first you're like, oh, this is fantastic.

42:56.788 --> 42:57.850
This is what I've been wanting.

42:58.230 --> 43:00.033
This is what I've wanted for so many years.

43:00.374 --> 43:07.224
I love 100% about this person until six months in, until a year in, certainly five years in.

43:07.244 --> 43:08.466
And all of a sudden you're like, oh, 80%.

43:09.314 --> 43:10.415
It's 20% that's missing.

43:11.397 --> 43:15.782
It's actually a different 20% than the 20% you were missing before, but it's still 20%.

43:17.944 --> 43:20.588
Stop chasing the elusive 20%.

43:21.108 --> 43:29.478
There is not a person who has ever walked on this planet outside of Jesus Christ who's going to give you 100% of what you need.

43:31.040 --> 43:35.986
Jesus Christ is the only one who can meet 100% of your needs.

43:36.962 --> 43:42.147
One of the smartest decisions that Sarah and I made when we first got married was we said this, we are not going to utter the D word.

43:43.388 --> 43:47.432
That means if we're in a fight, I'm not gonna threaten like, well, just divorce me then, or fine, that's how I feel.

43:47.612 --> 43:48.513
Let's just get a divorce.

43:48.753 --> 43:50.135
We don't use that word.

43:50.855 --> 43:51.656
It's off the table.

43:52.937 --> 43:53.578
Here's what that means.

43:53.598 --> 43:56.801
That means I'm either happily married or I'm unhappily married.

43:57.041 --> 43:58.222
Those are my two choices.

43:59.503 --> 44:03.047
It's amazing how motivated you are to work on your marriage when those are your two choices.

44:04.448 --> 44:06.450
And maybe you're here today and you've been through a divorce.

44:07.394 --> 44:10.419
And I'm always sensitive when we talk about this, because I know there's some shame in that.

44:10.459 --> 44:11.561
I don't want you to feel that at all.

44:12.282 --> 44:13.544
I want you to know our church loves you.

44:14.565 --> 44:16.168
We have a ministry called divorce care.

44:16.188 --> 44:18.752
I was just talking to a woman a couple of weeks ago who was a part of this.

44:18.772 --> 44:23.720
She said, it's helping me so much to be around other people who've gone through that situation and walked through that situation.

44:24.781 --> 44:25.462
We love you.

44:25.482 --> 44:27.686
We want to walk with you through that time of your life.

44:28.407 --> 44:31.812
Here's the second way that you can overcome and have a marriage for the long haul.

44:31.832 --> 44:35.378
It says, commit to working on your own stuff.

44:36.194 --> 44:37.436
This doesn't just apply to marriages.

44:37.456 --> 44:40.260
This applies to any relationship, dating relationship, friend relationship.

44:40.480 --> 44:40.880
Here's why.

44:41.321 --> 44:43.865
Healthy relationships are made of healthy people.

44:45.867 --> 44:48.070
If you're in a relationship right now, it's not a healthy relationship.

44:48.190 --> 44:49.252
You're 50% of that.

44:49.292 --> 44:51.034
It's either you, it's them, or it's both of you.

44:51.355 --> 44:53.558
But healthy relationships are made up of what?

44:53.798 --> 44:55.701
They are made up of healthy people.

44:56.942 --> 44:58.965
In Colossians chapter three, here's what Paul says.

44:59.206 --> 45:02.450
He says, get rid of sexual sin, impurity and lust.

45:04.386 --> 45:07.390
Do you know how many relationships have been ruined because of sexual sin?

45:08.892 --> 45:12.017
And we do, we just sort of watch it on TV shows and movies and it's just no big deal.

45:12.037 --> 45:13.198
It's like, oh, everybody's kind of hooking up.

45:13.218 --> 45:13.499
It's great.

45:13.519 --> 45:16.182
And no harm, you know, no foul, no consequence.

45:16.202 --> 45:26.817
I can't tell you in real life, when you step into real people's lives and you're just watching on a screen from Hollywood or a script, how many times sexual sin ruins relationships?

45:28.119 --> 45:28.920
He said, get rid of it.

45:28.960 --> 45:29.661
Get rid of greed.

45:30.002 --> 45:33.106
Get rid of anger, rage and filthy language.

45:35.042 --> 45:39.869
Do you know how many relationships have been ruined because of rage and anger?

45:42.632 --> 45:45.316
How many relationships have been destroyed because of someone's anger?

45:46.538 --> 45:47.799
You may say, well, it's not my stuff.

45:48.120 --> 45:51.545
It's his, it's hers, it's their sexual sin, it's their anger.

45:51.565 --> 45:56.371
I wanna show you a clip from author Sheila Walsh.

45:56.391 --> 45:58.174
Her and her husband were going through a difficult time.

45:58.214 --> 46:01.458
They were gonna go see a counselor, take a look at what she says.

46:03.746 --> 46:07.552
I was just thinking, Barry and I have been married for 31 years this year.

46:08.413 --> 46:15.183
But a few years back, we went to a really, a really difficult place where I didn't think we were going to survive.

46:15.564 --> 46:17.266
And I didn't want to survive.

46:17.687 --> 46:19.410
Because I felt like, you know what, this is too much.

46:20.351 --> 46:24.077
And he asked if I would be willing to go to counseling.

46:24.097 --> 46:25.198
And I'm like, well, I'll go if you want.

46:25.299 --> 46:27.181
The time I got in there, Barry had already been there.

46:27.342 --> 46:31.007
And he was in literally floods of tears.

46:31.067 --> 46:32.850
I could tell he was really broken.

46:33.282 --> 46:34.864
And the counselor asked him how he was doing.

46:34.884 --> 46:36.486
And he said, I'm not doing great.

46:36.867 --> 46:39.991
I've made some mistakes again that I promised I never would.

46:40.171 --> 46:43.175
And they said to me, and how are you doing?

46:43.195 --> 46:44.758
And I'm like, well, you know what?

46:44.778 --> 46:46.880
I'm just moving on.

46:47.982 --> 46:52.108
And then the counselor said to me, OK, let me tell you something.

46:52.128 --> 46:53.069
I have a friend.

46:53.670 --> 46:58.596
And when I asked my friend, who is your favorite person on this earth?

46:59.798 --> 47:01.080
And my friend said, my Taylor.

47:02.361 --> 47:02.802
And he said,

47:03.042 --> 47:05.005
Why is your tailor your favorite person?

47:05.326 --> 47:08.932
He said, because every time I go to him, he takes fresh measurements.

47:10.255 --> 47:13.901
I'm never what I was in this man, this godly kind man.

47:13.941 --> 47:15.564
Looked me nice at Sheila.

47:16.225 --> 47:17.688
Could you take fresh measurements?

47:18.369 --> 47:18.990
Oh, gosh.

47:19.010 --> 47:20.493
And I said, I can't take it.

47:20.513 --> 47:20.893
Oh, yeah.

47:20.973 --> 47:21.454
Well done.

47:21.474 --> 47:22.055
It's always.

47:22.075 --> 47:23.117
And I said, yes, I could.

47:23.518 --> 47:24.239
We done.

47:24.259 --> 47:25.842
Because it's like,

47:26.178 --> 47:27.500
The Holy Spirit gets us.

47:27.540 --> 47:28.181
I mean, He knows.

47:28.221 --> 47:29.783
I mean, I was not in a good place.

47:29.803 --> 47:31.004
I was mad.

47:31.044 --> 47:31.685
I was angry.

47:31.705 --> 47:32.246
I was hurt.

47:32.286 --> 47:33.227
I was disappointed.

47:33.708 --> 47:35.971
And all I wanted was for Him to know that.

47:36.892 --> 47:42.399
But when you say, when you invite the Holy Spirit into that dialogue, if you know what, if I couldn't with myself, we're in trouble here.

47:42.419 --> 47:45.103
And He kindly comes with you, you know?

47:49.048 --> 47:50.450
Could you take new measurements today?

47:54.146 --> 48:00.916
You might have a record of wrongs and bitterness in your heart that's been stored up for years, but could you take fresh measurements?

48:03.280 --> 48:05.303
Could you invite the Holy Spirit into your marriage?

48:07.406 --> 48:14.196
It's worth noting that her husband seems like he had repented and taken responsibility, and you might be in a different situation, and that is a different situation.

48:15.498 --> 48:17.882
And in those situations, there might be some boundaries that need to be set up.

48:17.902 --> 48:20.466
That might be the most loving thing you can do, but even then,

48:21.730 --> 48:24.474
You can invite the Holy Spirit into your marriage.

48:25.275 --> 48:26.717
Here's the third way to go the long haul.

48:26.857 --> 48:30.122
I'm gonna give to my spouse even if they don't do the same for me.

48:31.143 --> 48:33.727
I wanna show you this in the Bible, because it's a principle all of our scripture.

48:34.068 --> 48:37.653
Romans 5 verse eight says, while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

48:39.395 --> 48:43.141
Before we had done anything, he made the first move.

48:43.161 --> 48:44.202
Here's what it says in Ephesians.

48:44.282 --> 48:47.306
Husbands love your wives, just as Christ loved the church and what?

48:47.647 --> 48:49.810
He gave up his life for her.

48:51.586 --> 48:54.169
Jesus didn't wait for the church to make the first move.

48:54.230 --> 48:55.411
We didn't take the initiative.

48:55.692 --> 48:56.653
He took the initiative.

48:57.013 --> 48:58.716
He went first.

48:59.677 --> 49:03.542
I've told this story before, but several years ago, about 10 years ago, Sarah and I were on a date with each other.

49:04.003 --> 49:05.725
We were getting some ice cream at Sebastian Joe's.

49:06.526 --> 49:08.108
And there was this really long line.

49:08.128 --> 49:09.470
It was kind of out the door.

49:09.530 --> 49:10.612
It was a beautiful summer night.

49:11.072 --> 49:13.455
And so we got up to the front and we knew what we were gonna order.

49:13.876 --> 49:16.139
I was gonna order raspberry chocolate chip, which is the best.

49:16.900 --> 49:21.426
And Sarah was gonna offer, or get coffee ice cream, but they didn't have coffee ice cream.

49:22.050 --> 49:24.114
So we got up to the front and I'm like, I'll have raspberry chocolate chips.

49:24.134 --> 49:25.596
She said, I'll have coffee, ice cream.

49:25.796 --> 49:26.918
They said, oh, we're out of coffee.

49:26.958 --> 49:29.002
And now Sarah's flustered.

49:29.022 --> 49:29.944
She doesn't know what she wants.

49:30.785 --> 49:32.829
So she takes a sample of the basil vanilla.

49:32.849 --> 49:34.371
She takes a sample of the maple nut.

49:34.692 --> 49:38.138
She takes a sample of the honey cinnamon crisp.

49:38.158 --> 49:40.281
And I'm looking at the line of people behind us.

49:41.363 --> 49:42.525
And this is my issue.

49:42.605 --> 49:42.786
Okay.

49:42.806 --> 49:43.988
I'm not throwing her under the bus.

49:44.008 --> 49:45.150
I'm saying this is my issue.

49:45.510 --> 49:47.634
I care way too much what other people think.

49:48.674 --> 49:53.599
But I wanted them all to know I don't approve of all this crazy sampling that's going on here.

49:54.020 --> 49:54.180
Okay.

49:55.341 --> 49:55.902
This isn't me.

49:55.962 --> 49:56.302
It's her.

49:57.343 --> 49:58.744
And I wanted them all to know that.

49:59.866 --> 50:07.574
And so when her back was turned to me or so I thought, I kind of went like this, like to the line, just performatively to let them know it's not me.

50:09.255 --> 50:12.259
Right as I did that, Sarah turned to ask me a question.

50:13.460 --> 50:15.602
So she saw me kind of go like that.

50:16.578 --> 50:18.040
She turns, she goes, I'll take that.

50:18.120 --> 50:19.501
First one, salty caramel.

50:20.703 --> 50:21.644
She didn't like salty caramel.

50:23.065 --> 50:26.229
I know that because she told me several times that night that she didn't like salty caramel.

50:29.212 --> 50:30.393
And so we went outside.

50:30.453 --> 50:32.696
We'd been married for 10 years or 14 years at the time.

50:32.736 --> 50:34.118
We've been married 24 years now.

50:35.519 --> 50:37.081
And it's supposed to be this really beautiful night.

50:37.101 --> 50:37.722
We got ice cream.

50:37.742 --> 50:38.683
We're sitting with each other.

50:38.723 --> 50:39.423
No kids.

50:40.725 --> 50:41.746
And we are so ticked.

50:42.562 --> 50:44.925
I'm so frustrated that she took all that time.

50:44.985 --> 50:45.966
I was embarrassed.

50:45.986 --> 50:50.472
She's so mad at me for being rude and showing her up in front of all these other people.

50:50.832 --> 50:52.034
We are so ticked at each other.

50:52.374 --> 50:54.797
I'm just trying to wolf down my ice cream so I can get home.

50:56.559 --> 50:58.922
And I wish I could tell you that we worked it out really quickly.

50:58.962 --> 51:05.210
But when we got home, I was sitting on the couch and she came and sat next to me and she said, I don't like salty caramel.

51:06.332 --> 51:07.853
But this time she had a smile on her face.

51:09.716 --> 51:11.538
And we worked it out and we reconciled.

51:13.154 --> 51:16.298
but I realized afterwards that I had never apologized.

51:18.100 --> 51:19.101
I didn't take the first step.

51:19.161 --> 51:20.662
I didn't say, hey, I was so rude back there.

51:20.703 --> 51:21.944
I should not have done that.

51:21.964 --> 51:23.045
She loved me first.

51:24.727 --> 51:25.728
She went anyway.

51:27.630 --> 51:30.373
What if you didn't wait for your spouse to start loving you?

51:30.413 --> 51:31.114
You just love them.

51:32.235 --> 51:38.583
What if you didn't wait for them to start putting time and energy and effort into the relationship?

51:38.603 --> 51:41.586
What if you just started putting time and energy into the relationship?

51:43.490 --> 51:44.392
What if you went first?

51:45.895 --> 51:51.969
I had a tight chance to sit down with two couples that have been married for a long time and who I look up to and respect.

51:52.710 --> 51:56.458
These are the kind of couples that their marriage is the kind of marriage you're going, yeah, that's the kind of marriage I want someday.

51:57.200 --> 51:59.966
And so I sat down and had a chance to talk with them about this.

52:00.006 --> 52:01.249
I think you're going to enjoy their wisdom.

52:01.289 --> 52:01.810
Take a look.

52:13.250 --> 52:14.572
Well, thank you guys for your time.

52:14.592 --> 52:17.456
I really appreciate this to hear some wisdom about marriage.

52:17.676 --> 52:22.363
And I just think it's so important for couples in our church to hear what does it take to be married over the long haul.

52:22.403 --> 52:26.008
And so, we'd love for you guys to introduce yourselves and then to tell us how long you've been married.

52:26.709 --> 52:28.291
Byron Emmert and my wife, Linda.

52:29.112 --> 52:30.174
And how long have we been married?

52:30.414 --> 52:30.895
Long time.

52:30.955 --> 52:31.536
Long time.

52:32.177 --> 52:32.657
Going on 49.

52:32.697 --> 52:34.240
49 years.

52:34.480 --> 52:35.221
Phenomenal.

52:35.241 --> 52:38.866
Yeah, Jim and Jen Johnson and we've been married 31 years.

52:39.074 --> 52:44.221
What I love about this conversation is I think for so many couples in our church, they're in marriage right now, and it's difficult.

52:44.541 --> 52:47.445
And they look at you and go, how did you make it 49 years?

52:47.505 --> 52:48.887
How did you make it 31 years?

52:49.228 --> 52:52.732
What have you done to have an enduring marriage, a healthy marriage over the years?

52:52.752 --> 52:55.095
What are some of the things that you guys have built into your relationship?

52:56.157 --> 52:56.998
I've said this for years.

52:57.098 --> 52:59.161
The hardest job you sign up for is marriage.

52:59.681 --> 53:02.766
And someone told us years ago, base it around prayer.

53:03.246 --> 53:06.130
I know that sounds like the simple church answer, but

53:06.466 --> 53:13.836
when we've had struggles or challenges or even in the good times, going back to that and just saying, all right, we gotta bring this to the Lord in prayer.

53:13.936 --> 53:25.573
When we take time away from our schedule and just pray together out loud to the Lord, I just feel like it really, God changes our hearts, changes my heart sometimes, changes Jim's heart sometimes.

53:25.613 --> 53:32.202
I don't know who came up with it, but the triangle illustration really made a difference in our marriage.

53:33.103 --> 53:35.186
If this is me and here's Linda,

53:35.618 --> 53:36.579
And here's Jesus.

53:37.260 --> 53:45.633
If every day, if my purpose is to grow closer to Jesus and Linda's is the same, well, then naturally we grow closer to each other.

53:46.574 --> 53:51.321
And if one of us veers off, you notice it in our marriage.

53:51.441 --> 53:58.732
In fact, I've been convinced that intimacy in marriage will be proportionate to our intimacy with Christ.

53:59.473 --> 54:03.058
What are some of the habits or practices that have helped you guys communicate well with each other?

54:03.362 --> 54:14.277
Making sure we have a touch point every day that we just ask each other how we're doing, how our heart is, and praying together too has always been really helpful and good.

54:14.897 --> 54:18.703
Well, I know we've talked about listening, listening well, right?

54:18.723 --> 54:21.006
So, I mean, actively listening.

54:21.066 --> 54:25.912
So you're asking questions as you're listening and just following up with the person.

54:26.072 --> 54:30.258
So not just talking about your day, but asking about theirs.

54:30.370 --> 54:39.950
Just pursuing that listenership, if you will, because so often we talk about practicing communication, but it's really an art form to listen to each other.

54:39.990 --> 54:42.275
What do you guys do to keep pursuing each other over time?

54:43.117 --> 54:45.682
Yeah, I think making sure that it's calendared out.

54:46.023 --> 54:51.314
I mean, whether you get into a rhythm, some couples are able to do it weekly, some monthly, some maybe not.

54:51.650 --> 54:59.027
that often, but from day one said, how do we schedule out time throughout the week and throughout the month and throughout the year for each other?

54:59.307 --> 55:05.702
Someone told us and we're so thankful that they did make this, after your relationship with Jesus, the first priority.

55:06.624 --> 55:07.506
And your kids see that.

55:07.618 --> 55:10.421
They noticed that, and they see that for their own life.

55:10.622 --> 55:14.587
Yeah, and someday when your kids are gone, you still want to like each other, right?

55:14.607 --> 55:14.687
Yes.

55:15.007 --> 55:19.873
And hang out with each other, so we should be working on that relationship first, so.

55:19.893 --> 55:22.757
How do you guys navigate disagreement or disappointment?

55:22.777 --> 55:27.483
You know, you have something that you disagree about, or you're really just discouraged about it in your marriage?

55:27.523 --> 55:30.646
Like, talk through how do you guys work to navigate through that?

55:31.047 --> 55:34.571
We did have pre-marriage counseling, and so she was amazing.

55:34.732 --> 55:36.754
The first thing she said to us was,

55:36.930 --> 55:38.351
don't blame the other person.

55:38.391 --> 55:45.639
Instead of saying, you always do this, or you never do this, or you're driving me crazy, you say, when you do this, it makes me feel.

55:45.919 --> 55:46.840
This is how I feel.

55:46.900 --> 55:48.802
And so those feelings are legitimate.

55:48.962 --> 55:58.811
And so to express your feelings to each other, and then just reciprocating and listening to each other through that sharing time too.

55:58.832 --> 56:05.458
If part of your story right now is that you're in the middle of a real struggle with your spouse or even separated,

56:05.698 --> 56:15.751
to really turn to the Lord yourself and to start with yourself and just go, am I being the person that God empowers me to be?

56:16.432 --> 56:17.133
Yeah, that's good.

56:17.774 --> 56:19.977
Hey, Jim and Jen, I want to ask you this question.

56:20.017 --> 56:22.260
Speak to that couple right now who's really struggling.

56:22.861 --> 56:25.464
I can't imagine how I would get to 31 or 49 years.

56:25.844 --> 56:27.026
What would you say to that couple?

56:27.650 --> 56:34.517
I think too many times if you just keep thinking about the negative things, the things that drive you crazy, then your whole mindset is gonna be negative.

56:34.997 --> 56:49.472
But if you can remember the positive things and just really focus on those, but I always go back to prayer to be in man, you just gotta surrender it to the Lord and pour out your heart to the Lord and give that spouse over to the Lord and God can change hearts.

56:49.692 --> 56:51.674
So I just, I really believe that.

56:52.395 --> 56:55.378
I think early in our marriage we thought because of our faith that

56:55.650 --> 56:57.172
Divorce would never happen to us.

56:57.212 --> 56:59.255
That just wasn't anything that could ever happen.

56:59.315 --> 57:09.771
And after a while, and having some of our good friends and that were strong believers and had faith, too, and their marriages were falling apart, we realized we're not immune.

57:09.971 --> 57:11.874
We have to work at this and keep working at it.

57:11.914 --> 57:13.617
It's not just going to happen naturally.

57:13.657 --> 57:22.770
What advice would you give your newlywed selves to believe what research shows that

57:23.042 --> 57:36.097
The three main areas of possible disagreement in a marriage, communication, money, and sex, be open in talking about those three areas and striving to see what God's perspective is.

57:36.938 --> 57:38.981
I would say, honestly, true confession.

57:39.221 --> 57:42.445
In my early years of our marriage, I'm recovering workaholic.

57:42.725 --> 57:48.953
I mean, I put so much time and energy into what I was doing outside the home, and I have regret for that.

57:48.973 --> 57:50.034
And yet,

57:50.530 --> 57:59.804
you know, slowly but surely dialed that in and I'm so thankful that it wasn't too far into our marriage where this became the number one priority after our relationship with God.

57:59.864 --> 58:03.951
And all the more you have to prioritize and continue to date.

58:05.052 --> 58:09.679
Date when you don't have kids, date while you have kids, date after your kids are out of the house.

58:09.759 --> 58:10.641
That's so critical.

58:11.582 --> 58:14.246
Thank you guys for your wisdom and your time in this.

58:14.326 --> 58:16.690
My prayer is for our church that their marriages

58:16.834 --> 58:20.519
would endure, and that they would have a marriage of being able to look back, because what a testimony it is.

58:21.159 --> 58:25.485
Your guys just have a great reputation for your marriage, and it's because, man, we all want that.

58:25.505 --> 58:27.387
We all want to be able to say, we've been married for 49 years.

58:27.407 --> 58:28.528
We've been married for 31 years.

58:28.569 --> 58:29.510
Look at what God has done.

58:29.550 --> 58:34.416
I'm just so thankful for you guys and how you have prioritized your marriage, and thanks for your wisdom today.

58:38.701 --> 58:39.722
That's what I want to do right now.

58:40.964 --> 58:42.706
I want to pray over the marriages in our church.

58:44.354 --> 58:49.863
And so if you're sitting next to your spouse and you feel comfortable doing that, maybe just a moment to hold hands during this prayer.

58:51.386 --> 58:55.733
And just to say, Hey, you and me, let's go to the long haul.

58:56.976 --> 58:57.617
Let's pray together.

58:57.637 --> 59:00.702
Lord, I thank you for every marriage.

59:02.305 --> 59:06.412
Thank you for our parents' marriage and our grandparents' marriages that have pointed us to you.

59:07.934 --> 59:10.098
And God, I pray that for every marriage in this room.

59:11.394 --> 59:15.701
even in difficult times, even in frustrating times, even in times when we don't feel loved or understood.

59:15.761 --> 59:23.854
Lord, would you give us your love and fill us with your hope?

59:25.697 --> 59:38.418
I pray over every marriage in this room, God, that you would strengthen it, that you would protect it, that we would prioritize it, God, and that we would experience the blessing that comes when you said that

59:39.938 --> 59:48.732
A man will leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife that we would experience the blessing of oneness and that our kids would see that and our grandchildren would see that.

59:48.752 --> 59:53.479
God, would you use our marriage to start a legacy for our family?

59:55.262 --> 59:59.488
God, I thank you that you loved us first and you pursued us first.

01:00:00.991 --> 01:00:02.233
Pray all these things in Jesus' name.

01:00:03.194 --> 01:00:03.434
Amen.

01:00:04.075 --> 01:00:04.997
Have a great weekend everyone.

01:00:05.017 --> 01:00:05.778
We'll see you next week.

